{{for|Basque pony|Pottok}} {{use dmy dates|date=June 2014}} {{use list-defined references|date=June 2014}} {{Use British English|date=June 2014}} {{Infobox horse breed |name= Basque Mountain Horse |image=File:Arraba 001 zaldiletsua.jpg |image_caption=On [[Gorbeia]] | image2 = | image_size2 = | image_alt2 = | image_caption2 = | features = | altname= {{ubl|{{lang-eu|{{noitalic|Euskal Herriko Mendiko Zaldia}}}}|{{lang-es|{{noitalic|Caballo de Monte del País Vasco}}}}}} | nickname= | country=Spain, France | distribution =[[Basque Country (greater region)|Basque Country]] | use = | colour = | height = 138.5 cm{{r|standard}} | male_height = | female_height = | weight = | male_weight = | female_weight = | status = | note = |group1= [[MAPAMA]] (Spain) |std1= http://www.mapama.gob.es/es/ganaderia/temas/zootecnia/orden30-11-2015reglamentacioncaballodemonte_tcm7-297937.pdf }} [[File:Gorbea - Caballo 02.jpg|thumb|On [[Gorbeia]]]] [[File:Arraba 002 zaldiak.jpg|thumb|[[Mare]] and foal on Gorbeia]] The '''Basque Mountain Horse''' ({{lang-es|'Caballo de Monte del País Vasco'}}, {{lang-eu|{{noitalic|'''Euskal Herriko Mendiko Zaldia'''}}}}) is a breed of horse from the [[Basque Country (greater region)|Basque Country]] of [[Spain]] and [[France]]. It is listed in the Catálogo Oficial de Razas de Ganado de España, the official catalogue of livestock breeds of Spain, in the group of [[wikt:autochthonous|autochthonous]] breeds in danger of extinction.<ref name=magrama/> The original breed standard of the "Euskal Herriko Mendiko Zaldia / Caballo de Monte del País Vasco", officially approved on 21 July 1999 and published in the ''Boletín Oficial del País Vasco'', the official bulletin of the Basque Country, was repealed in 2015 and replaced with a new one.{{r|pinan|standard}}
At the end of 2013 the total number of breeding animals recorded in the herdbook was 4556.<ref name=magrama2/>
