'''Experience China''' (感知中国) is a serial culture event held by [[China]]'s [[State Council Information Office]] in foreign countries. A variety of activities, including performances, [[Chinese film]] week, [[television]] week, forums, [[Chinese food]] festival,etc. , are held during the event. Usually jointly held by the Ministry of Culture and embassies of both countries, the event was held in [[France]] in 1999 for the first time. Then in [[United States|U.S.]] in 2000, in [[Germany]] in 2001, in [[Russia]] in 2003, in [[Argentina]] in 2004, in [[South Korea]] in Sep. 2006, in [[South Africa]] in Nov. 2006, and in [[Israel]] in 2009.<ref>[http://english.cctv.com/program/cctvnews/20091019/101157.shtml "Experience China in Israel" kicks off to celebrate China-Israeli ties] CNTV news, Oct.-09-2009</ref> 

In October 2010, the event was held in three cities of [[Turkey]]: [[Ancyra]], [[Istanbul]] and [[Kayseri]].<ref>[http://english.cntv.cn/english/special/news/20100826/103081.shtml "Experience China" Turkey Tour to open in October] CNTV news, 08-26-2010</ref>

