'''Federación de Andinismo de Chile''' (FEACH) is an [[umbrella organization]] of [[Chile]]an [[mountaineering club]]s. Founded in 1942 as ''Federación de Ski y Andinismo de Chile'', it originally had six member clubs. In 1955, the skiing and the mountaineering sections were split and FEACH currently has more than 20 affiliated clubs around Chile.
