{{Infobox language |name=Paresi |altname=Arití |states=[[Brazil]] |region=[[Mato Grosso]] |speakers=2,000 |date=2008 |ref=e18 |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Maipurean languages|Arawakan]] |fam2=Southern ? |fam3=[[Paresi–Waura languages|Paresí–Xingu]] |fam4=Paresí languages |iso3=pab |glotto=pare1272 |glottorefname=Parecís }}
'''Paresí''' (Pareci) is an [[Arawakan languages|Arawakan language]] spoken in [[Brazil]].
Dialects are Caxinití, Waimaré, Kozariní, Uariteré.
